Pregnancies: Number of times the patient has been pregnant
Glucose: Plasma glucose concentration (mg/dL) after a 2-hour oral glucose tolerance test
SkinThickness: Triceps skinfold thickness (mm), used to estimate body fat
BMI: Body mass index, calculated as weight in kg divided by the square of height in meters (kg/m^2)
DiabetesPedigreeFunction: A function that scores the likelihood of diabetes based on family history
Age: Age of the patient in years
Outcome: Binary indicator of whether the patient has diabetes (1) or not (0)
